      • getResourceBundleBase

        public String getResourceBundleBase()
        Description copied from interface: ConfigurableJobBeanWrapper
        Since the job will be defined in a component outside of the job scheduler, the job scheduler has no knowledge of the keys nor the resource files to use when rendering these properties in the UI. Thus, the job should be configured in a wrapper which supplies a ResourceBundle to the job scheduler. That ResourceBundle will supply the strings to use in the UI.
        Specified by:
